Nice, this is fun. I’ll give you **5 Tailwind-ready HTML templates**, each as a standalone page you can drop into your stack or refactor into fastHTML.

They all share a similar visual language:

* dark-ish neutral background
* card-based layout
* mobile-first
* minimal, semantic markup
* ready for HTMX hooks later (`data-*` or `hx-*` are easy to add)

You can swap the Tailwind CDN for your build pipeline later.

